dc_title_s: Greenland Sea, Iceland--north coast, Eyjafjörður (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the National Imagery and Mapping Agency. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. "From U.S. surveys to 1994." Not distributed to depository libraries. "Copyright 1998 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Place names in Icelandic with glossary in English. Insets: Siglufjordur. Scale 1:12,500. Akureyri. Scale 1:10,000. Map no.38681. This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA). United States. National Imagery and Mapping Agency. (1998). Greenland Sea, Iceland--north coast, Eyjafjörður (Raster Image). LandInfo. Available at: https://purl.stanford.edu/zz276tk7676 This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
